<li id="cite_note-nobel91-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink noprint">↑ <sup><a href="#cite_ref-nobel91_2-0">a</a> et <a href="#cite_ref-nobel91_2-1">b</a></sup> </span><span class="reference-text">Nobel Prize in Physics 1991<span class="ouvrage"><abbr class="abbr indicateur-langue" title="Langue : anglais">(en)</abbr> <span lang="en"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/physics/laureates/1991/">«&#160;<cite style="font-style:normal;">Nobel prize in Physics 1991</cite>&#160;»</a></span> <small style="line-height:1em;">(consulté le <span class="nowrap">31 mars 2016</span>)</small></span>&#160;: <span class="citation">«&#160;<span class="lang-en" lang="en">for discovering that methods developed for studying order phenomena in simple systems can be generalized to more complex forms of matter, in particular to liquid crystals and polymers</span>&#160;»</span>.</span>
